# Product Flow Fidelity Rule

When editing UI/API behavior, preserve high fidelity to approved intake/product/flow artifacts.

- Treat `docs/agent-artifacts/00-intake/`, `01-product/`, `02-design/`, `03-architecture/`, and `04-data/` as source of truth.
- Do not redesign flows on your own unless explicitly requested.
- Match approved screen/flow structure, state transitions, and role permissions.
- Implement all intended states: loading, empty, error, success, disabled.
- If a detail is missing, infer the smallest reasonable change and record deviation.
